It&#x27;s for Google Analytics tracking of links. The links in the page use Javascript:<p><pre><code>  <a onclick=&quot;goTracked(&quot;link-external&quot;, &quot;http://octopart.com/bb-bblk-000-circuitco+electronics-26478322&quot;);&quot; class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;#http://octopart.com/bb-bblk-000-circuitco+electronics-26478322&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>BeagleBone Black is readily available all over the world</a>
</code></pre>
then the Javascript function in question:<p><pre><code>  function goTracked(action, link) {
    ga(&#x27;send&#x27;, &#x27;event&#x27;, &#x27;exit&#x27;, action, link);
    setTimeout(&#x27;document.location = &quot;&#x27; + link + &#x27;&quot;&#x27;, 100);
  }
</code></pre>
So, if you try to Cmd-Click a link to open it in a new tab (or middle-click, which is my preferred method), the target of the link is opened in a new tab. But the link&#x27;s &quot;href&quot; target is just a fragment, so it opens the article in the new tab. 100 ms later, the current tab is redirected to the &quot;actual&quot; link target.
